⊕meta⊕
name = "triage-failed-sky-run"
description = "Read a failed sky run's logs, pinpoint the failing node + root cause in the .sky source, and propose a fix diff plus the command to apply it (nothing is auto-applied)."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
max_budget_usd = 2.0
⊕⊕

§fetch§
bash_file = "./scripts/fetch.sh"
§§

§diagnose§
model = "sonnet"
depends_on = ["fetch"]
skills = ["sky-workflow-authoring"]
§§

§propose§
model = "sonnet"
depends_on = ["diagnose"]
chain_from = "diagnose"
§§

∆diagnose∆
A sky run failed. Read the workflow source at {{dir}}/{{name}}.sky, then read the run logs + source captured below (logs are best-effort and may be partial or unavailable):

$SKY_OUTPUT_FETCH

Tasks:
1. Identify the failing node (its §id§) from the logs. If the logs do not name a node, say so and infer the most likely culprit from the source + any error text.
2. State the root cause concretely: which line/config/bash/prompt caused the failure and why.
3. Note your confidence and which evidence (log line vs. source inference) it rests on.

Keep it terse and machine-oriented. Do NOT edit any file.
∆∆

∆propose∆
Using your diagnosis above, produce a concrete remediation. Do NOT edit, write, or run anything — output only.

Emit exactly two sections:

1. A unified diff for {{dir}}/{{name}}.sky that fixes the root cause. Use standard `diff -u` format with `---`/`+++` headers and `@@` hunks so it can be reviewed and applied by hand. Change only what is required.

2. The exact command to apply the fix via the update workflow, on one line:
   sky run update-sky-workflow --var dir={{dir}} --var name={{name}} --var request="<one-line description of the change>"
   Fill in the request with a precise, single-sentence instruction describing the fix.

If the failure is environmental (missing run id, daemon down, transient) rather than a source defect, say so plainly and skip the diff. Keep prose minimal.
∆∆

※※
triage-failed-sky-run — diagnose a failed run + propose (not apply) a fix

DAG:
  fetch ──> diagnose ──(chain_from)──> propose

  fetch     bash: confirm the .sky exists; best-effort `sky logs <run>`; cat the source
  diagnose  claude(sonnet): read source + failure output, name the failing node + root cause
  propose   claude(sonnet, chained from diagnose): output a unified diff + the apply command

Run:
  sky run triage-failed-sky-run --var dir=.sky/workflows --var name=my-workflow --var run=<run-id>

Vars:
  dir   directory containing the .sky file
  name  workflow filename without .sky
  run   the failed run id (required)

Notes:
  - A run id is required (--var run); without it fetch exits nonzero.
  - Node-level failure extraction from logs is best-effort: if `sky logs` is unavailable
    or does not name the node, diagnose infers the culprit from the source + error text.
  - Nothing is auto-applied. propose only prints a diff + the update-sky-workflow command;
    review and run that command yourself to apply the fix.
※※
